cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper investigates the inductive biases of standard neural architectures in the context of language learning, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on language learning and the mutual exclusivity bias. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely, as the paper discusses the inductive biases of neural networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category, as the paper explores how neural networks can learn in fast and adaptable ways. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper discusses how neural networks map words to referents. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper discusses the design of neural networks.
